AGENTS.md byte-ceiling guard (looper-bloat backstop): gm test.js checkAgentsMdBudget() asserts AGENTS.md <= 36000 bytes AND contains at least one `recall:` pointer, wired into main() alongside checkNoBom/checkNoComments. RATIONALE: looper's AGENTS.md grew to 79610 bytes (2.9x gm's ~27.5k) DESPITE having .gm/rs-learn.db present -- the migration target existed but nothing enforced the bidirectional-drain back-pressure, so detail-heavy single-crate entries accreted inline instead of draining to recall pointers. The ceiling makes that failure mode structurally unrepresentable (Principle 8): a build fails the moment AGENTS.md bloats, forcing a drain of a detail-heavy entry to a one-line recall: pointer (memorize-fire the substance) rather than letting prose accumulate. Ceiling=36000 gives headroom over the ~27.5k floor of legit top-level cross-cutting rules. Never compress a top-level rule to make budget; the drain target is always over-verbose detail/pointers.